hw7

Class MinimumCostPathFinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • hw7.MinimumCostPathFinder

  • public class MinimumCostPathFinder
extends Object
    MinimumCostPathFinder finds the minimum-cost path between two nodes on a weighted graph. Mininum cost path is defined as a path with the least overall weight, with ties broken by least path length. At each step the least next node value is chosen, and ties are broken with the least edge weights.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Bryan Yue

      • djkPath

        public static <T extends Comparable<T>> MinimumCostPathFinder.Path<T> djkPath(T source,
                                                                              T dest,
                                                                              hw5.Graph<T,Double> g)
        Finds the minimum-cost between two nodes, searching by lexicographically least destination and breaking ties with lowest edge weights.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the node data
        Parameters:
        source - the T label of the source node.
        dest - the T label of the destination node.
        g - the weighted graph to find the shortest path on.
        Returns:
        the mininum-cost path from the source to destination character with associated weights. Returns null if the source, dest, or g is null. Also returns null if the source or dest is not in g. Also returns null if no path was found. If the source is the destination too, a new empty path is returned.
